cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CG, cs.IT, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with distance labeling schemes for trees, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and graph theory (cs.DM, cs.CG). It also involves information theory (cs.IT) in terms of the number of bits required for the labels, and potentially social networks (cs.SI) as trees can be used to model certain types of social networks.
